{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at module handoff: collectors + aggregation + summary-input builder. An in-process test with three source adapters (stubbed responses) can catch missing/overwritten sections. Rejected System because behavior text only requires that payload includes all three sources, not real network/OS effects. Rejected Agentic because it checks pre-summary input assembly, not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire real data-collection modules to a real aggregation function and a stub summary generator that records its input. Feed distinct fixtures from metrics endpoint client, issue tracker client, and deployment log reader; assert the recorded summary input contains all three source payloads with correct section mapping.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback formatting (source adapter failure -> report composer behavior). A fake failing adapter reproduces the failure boundary without real network. Rejected System because behavior text says only 'one data source is unavailable' and expected fallback note, not transport-level/network-stack behavior. Rejected Agentic because requirement is fallback control-flow, not LLM judgment.","test_description":"Run report assembly with two normal source adapters and one adapter that raises an unavailable error. Assert run completes, output contains `data unavailable` note in the failed section, and other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generated narrative content fidelity to input values; stubs would always pass and hide model misrepresentation. This is LLM/model-output quality, not just wrapper logic. Rejected Workflow because behavior names a single summary-generation decision, not multiple agentic stages in sequence.","test_description":"Use representative real input datasets and call the real summary-generation model. Score whether key numeric/status values are preserved (exact/near-exact extraction checks over generated text) across repeated runs with acceptance thresholds for accuracy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires real end-to-end delivery to an inbox, which crosses real HTTP/network/email infrastructure. In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, provider acceptance, and inbox delivery issues. Rejected Agentic because the stated failure boundary is delivery to inbox, not evaluation of model output quality.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script against reachable test instances of the three data sources and a real email delivery path to a test mailbox. Assert the mailbox receives one message addressed to configured recipients with expected report sections present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is orchestration across local modules: mailer failure handling, local persistence, and retry state on next run. This can be caught with a failing mailer stub plus real local filesystem in-process wiring. Rejected System because behavior text does not require validating real network outage characteristics, only unreachable-result handling and retry behavior.","test_description":"Run script once with mailer adapter configured to return unreachable error; assert report is written to fallback local file and marked pending retry. Run script again with mailer restored; assert pending report is sent and retry artifact/state is cleared.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.52,"System":0.38,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
